    • Method Detail

      • extension

        public WebSocketExtension extension()
        Returns the parent WebSocketExtension that this parameter is defined in.
        Returns:
        String name of the extension

      • anonymous

        public boolean anonymous()
        Indicates whether the parameter is anonymous or named. If the parameter is anonymous and it is not transient, then it's name is NOT put on the wire during the handshake. However, it's value is put on the wire.
        Returns:
        boolean true if the parameter is anonymous, false if the parameter is named

      • metadata

        public EnumSet<WebSocketExtension.Parameter.Metadata> metadata()
        Returns the metadata characteristics of this extension parameter. The returned EnumSet is a clone so any changes to it will not be picked by by the extension parameter.
        Returns:
        EnumSet characteristics of the extension parameter

      • name

        public String name()
        Returns the name of the parameter.
        Returns:
        String name of the parameter

      • required

        public boolean required()
        Indicates whether the parameter is required. If the required parameter is not set, then the extension is not negotiated during the handshake.
        Returns:
        boolean true if the parameter is required, otherwise false

      • temporal

        public boolean temporal()
        Indicates whether the parameter is temporal/transient. Temporal parameters are not put on the wire during the handshake.
        Returns:
        boolean true if the parameter is temporal, otherwise false

      • type

        public Class<T> type()
        Returns the type of the parameter.
        Returns:
        Class type of the parameter
